# Load the dataset from GEO
geo_dataset <- getGEO("GSE234762", GSEMatrix = TRUE)
## Found 1 file(s)
## GSE234762_series_matrix.txt.gz
expr_data <- fread("RNAseq_exp_data.tsv", sep = "\t", header = TRUE)
series_matrix <- fread("C:/Users/Admin/OneDrive - Teesside University/Desktop/GBM_DEG_analysis/Human.GRCh38.p13.annot.tsv", sep = "\t", header = TRUE)
# Merge expression data with gene annotation based on GeneID
merged_data <- merge(series_matrix, expr_data, by = "GeneID")
# Keep only the "Symbol" column and the last 4 columns (expression data)
merged_data <- merged_data[, c("Symbol", "GSM7474303", "GSM7474304", "GSM7474305", "GSM7474306")]
#colnames(merged_data)

metadata <- pData(geo_dataset[[1]])  # Extract sample metadata
# Define a named vector for mapping sample titles to groups
group_mapping <- c(
  "GBM8401 cells (bio rep1)" = "Sensitive",
  "GBM8401 cells (bio rep2)" = "Sensitive",
  "GBM8401 TMZ-resistant cells (bio rep1)" = "Resistant",
  "GBM8401 TMZ-resistant cells (bio rep2)" = "Resistant"
)

# Assign groups based on the title column
metadata$group <- group_mapping[metadata$title]


# Remove the geneID column from the expression data
expr_data <- merged_data[, -1]  


# Convert 'group' to a factor with "Disease" as the reference level
metadata$group <- factor(metadata$group, levels = c("Sensitive", "Resistant"))

# Create DESeq2 dataset
dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = expr_data, 
                              colData = metadata, 
                              design = ~ group)

# Run DESeq2 differential expression(DE) analysis
dds <- DESeq(dds)
## estimating size factors
## estimating dispersions
## gene-wise dispersion estimates
## mean-dispersion relationship
## final dispersion estimates
## fitting model and testing
DE_result <- results(dds, contrast = c("group", "Resistant", "Sensitive"))
#
res_df <- as.data.frame(DE_result)  
res_df$Symbol <- rownames(res_df)
# Merge res_df with merged_data by row names
annotated_result <- merge(res_df, merged_data, by = "row.names", all.x = TRUE)
# Remove the Row.names column 
annotated_result <- annotated_result[, -1]
merged_result <- annotated_result[, c(1:6, which(names(annotated_result) == "Symbol.y"))]

# Filter significant DEGs (adjusted p-value < 0.05, |logFC| > 1)
deg_result <- as.data.frame(merged_result) %>%
  filter(padj < 0.05 & abs(log2FoldChange) > 2)


# Ensure the Entrez IDs are correctly extracted
Gse234762_result_table <- fread("GSE234762.top.tables.tsv", sep = "\t", header = TRUE)
entrez_ids <- as.character(Gse234762_result_table$GeneID)  

# Remove any NA values
entrez_ids <- na.omit(entrez_ids)

valid_ids <- entrez_ids[entrez_ids %in% keys(org.Hs.eg.db, keytype = "ENTREZID")]
cat("Number of valid Entrez IDs:", length(valid_ids), "\n")
## Number of valid Entrez IDs: 19233
# GO Enrichment Analysis (Biological Process)
go_results <- enrichGO(gene = valid_ids,
                       OrgDb = org.Hs.eg.db, 
                       keyType = "ENTREZID", 
                       ont = "BP",  # Change to "MF" or "CC" if needed
                       pAdjustMethod = "BH", 
                       pvalueCutoff = 0.05,  # Increase cutoff
                       qvalueCutoff = 0.05)

# GO Enrichment Analysis (Molecular functions)
go_results_MF <- enrichGO(gene = valid_ids,
                          OrgDb = org.Hs.eg.db, 
                          keyType = "ENTREZID", 
                          ont = "MF",  # Change to "MF" or "CC" if needed
                          pAdjustMethod = "BH", 
                          pvalueCutoff = 0.05,  # Increase cutoff
                          qvalueCutoff = 0.05)

# GO Enrichment Analysis (Cellular components)
go_results_cc <- enrichGO(gene = valid_ids,
                          OrgDb = org.Hs.eg.db, 
                          keyType = "ENTREZID", 
                          ont = "CC",  # Change to "MF" or "CC" if needed
                          pAdjustMethod = "BH", 
                          pvalueCutoff = 0.05,  # Increase cutoff
                          qvalueCutoff = 0.05)

# Visualization of molecular function Enrichment Results
# GO Enrichment: Dot Plot
dotplot(go_results_MF, showCategory=20) + ggtitle("Top 20 GO Enriched Molecular Function")

# GO Enrichment: Bar Plot
barplot(go_results_MF, showCategory=20) + ggtitle("Top 20 GO Enriched Biological Processes")

# Visualization of cellular components Enrichment Results
# GO Enrichment: Dot Plot
dotplot(go_results_cc, showCategory=20) + ggtitle("Top 20 GO Enriched Cellular components")

# GO Enrichment: Bar Plot
barplot(go_results_cc, showCategory=20) + ggtitle("Top 20 GO Enriched Biological Processes")
